The paper focuses on the language grounding problem, which involves extracting representations of the meanings of natural language tied to perception and actuation in the physical world. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Robotics (cs.RO), and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents an approach for joint learning of language and perception models, which involves machine learning techniques and could be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
